```

When `cursor = new WorkerHandle(frame);` is called for the second time, the old `WorkerHandle` is lost without calling `close()`. Since `WorkerHandle.close()` calls `frame.unpin()`, the old `TimelineFrame` will never have its pin count drop to zero (once cooled), and thus `closeLoadedGeneration()` will never be called. This prevents the `URLClassLoader` from being closed, leading to Metaspace exhaustion.

